RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Special Weight Purse 38500. FOR REGISTERED INDIANA BREDS SIRED BY REGISTERED INDIANA STALLIONS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HALO LOVE stalked the pace from the three path through the turn, bid three wide nearing the eighth pole, gained the lead near the sixteenth pole and inched up. BIG CITY HEAT steadied soon after the start to shift to the outside of the pacesetter, pressed the pace two wide through the turn, bid into the lane, led with an eighth to go then was outfinished late. STAR REVIEW was in the three path through the turn, came into the lane from the four path, was slowly gaining late then benefitted a couple of spots when two rivals lost ground late. COMMANDO JOE raced in the two path through the turn while behind several, was boxed in looking for a path through the lane, shifted to the four path then back to the two path, went for a hole inside the sixteenth pole, was in tight and checked late. LUCKIES JOY ridden hard early to clear for the lead before the first call, was under pressure through mid-turn and into the lane, lost the lead inside the eighth pole, remained on the rail when another came over and put him in tight to the rail, was taken up late. DISTORTED NOTION trailed throughout while in the two or three path. A FTER A STEWARD'S INQUIRY AND AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF #4 LUCKIES JOY AGAINST THE RIDER OF #3 BID CITY HEAT FOR INTERFERENCE IN DEEP STRETCH THERE WAS NO CHANGE IN ORDER.

ENTRY.NAME: Halo Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3path, bid 3wd upper, long drive, inched up

ENTRY.NAME: Big City Heat
ENTRY.COMMENT: shifted 2wd, pressed turn, bid 2wd led, outfinished

ENTRY.NAME: Luckies Joy
ENTRY.OWNER: Claramunt, Dennis and Cynthia and Klopp, Randy
ENTRY.COMMENT: ridden early, clear pace, inside lane, shut off, checked late

ENTRY.NAME: Commando Joe
ENTRY.OWNER: Matthews Randy Farrell Charles and Reynolds William

RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 34000. (PLUS UP TO 40% Indiana State Bred Supplement) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. If this race is taken off the turf, it will be run at 5 furlongs on the main track. (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TX WOMEN FOR ARTS vied for the lead two wide through the turn, shook away into the lane, cleared when straightening then widened through the final eighth. WHATTA WORLD chased the two rival duel through the turn while in the three path ,came into the lane from the four path and moved up to be second best while not a threat to the top one. PRINCESS MITOLE vied for the lead with the winner through the turn then yielded coming into the lane but stayed on to be clear for the show spot. NO SHOW was in the three or four path through the turn when well back, came into the lane from the six or seven path, was six wide at the eighth pole and moved up to be best of the rest. TONIC AND GIN raced well back while in the two or three path through the turn, came into the lane from the six path and improved position while never a menace. MORNING GORDITA raced in the two path though the turn and lost ground throughout. KESSEL was in the three or four path while in mid-pack, came into the lane from the five path and tired. YOU'RE KITTEN ME raced along the inside when towards the back, was put in tight near the sixteenth pole, checked and never menaced. MAIREAD was in the two path through the turn when a contender, came into the lane from the three path and was done near the eighth pole. BAYTOWN BAMA GIRL was outrun while along the inside. NEW WOMAN was outrun while in the three or four path through the turn. HOLLYWOODBOULEVARD chased the pace along the inside through the turn and was empty turning into the lane.

ENTRY.OWNER: Baytown Partnership and Resolute Racing Alliance LLC

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GEORGIE W was unhurried while off the inside, moved into the far turn from the three path, bid three wide in mid-turn, quickly cleared in late turn, widened into the lane, continued to extend the advantage inside the eighth pole to some twelve lengths then geared down the last seventy yards. ROMAN GIANT raced along the inside down the backstretch when in a bunched field, moved off the inside and bid two wide and between the winner and pacesetter nearing the three-eighths pole, stayed with the top one until near the quarter pole then was no match while staying on for the distant place spot. TAKE CHARGE GENT was in the two path through the turn when never a threat. IRONSIDES set the pace into the far turn, was quickly passed by the top two rivals and was empty through the lane.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SASSY KATIE vied for the lead along the inside throughout, continued to duel through the lane and inched up late. CLEVER KATE saved ground throughout and was slowly gaining to the wire. SKIPPINJUSTICE raced in the four path when near the back, swung into the lane from the seven path and slowly gained while not a threat. DASH OF SIMPLICITY raced in the two path through the turn when in mid-pack then weakened after coming into the lane from the three path. NOBLE PRIZE settled into the three path through the far turn, came into the lane from the six path and never factored. TIZ ABBY was in the five to the four path through the first turn, moved closer to the inside through late turn and never made an impact. STORMY WAGER chased the two rival duel through the far turn when in the two or three path and was done nearing the quarter pole.
